{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":883,"text":"This is our life with bees,"},{"time":4863,"text":"and this is our life without bees."},{"time":8586,"text":"Bees are the most important pollinators"},{"time":11054,"text":"of our fruits and vegetables and flowers"},{"time":13863,"text":"and crops like alfalfa hay that feed our farm animals."},{"time":17522,"text":"More than one third of the world's crop production"},{"time":20210,"text":"is dependent on bee pollination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22992,"text":"But the ironic thing is that bees are not out there"},{"time":25829,"text":"pollinating our food intentionally."},{"time":28746,"text":"They're out there because they need to eat."},{"time":31617,"text":"Bees get all of the protein they need in their diet"},{"time":34336,"text":"from pollen"},{"time":35665,"text":"and all of the carbohydrates they need from nectar."},{"time":38601,"text":"They're flower-feeders,"},{"time":40366,"text":"and as they move from flower to flower,"},{"time":42300,"text":"basically on a shopping trip at the local floral mart,"},{"time":45771,"text":"they end up providing this valuable pollination service."},{"time":50226,"text":"In parts of the world where there are no bees,"},{"time":52746,"text":"or where they plant varieties that are not attractive to bees,"},{"time":55652,"text":"people are paid to do the business of pollination by hand."},{"time":59858,"text":"These people are moving pollen from flower to flower"},{"time":63542,"text":"with a paintbrush."},{"time":65441,"text":"Now this business of hand pollination"},{"time":67887,"text":"is actually not that uncommon."},{"time":69973,"text":"Tomato growers often pollinate their tomato flowers"},{"time":73325,"text":"with a hand-held vibrator."},{"time":75982,"text":"Now this one's the tomato tickler. (Laughter)"},{"time":79926,"text":"Now this is because the pollen within a tomato flower"},{"time":85206,"text":"is held very securely within"},{"time":86986,"text":"the male part of the flower, the anther,"},{"time":89486,"text":"and the only way to release this pollen is to vibrate it."},{"time":92860,"text":"So bumblebees are one of the few kinds of bees in the world"},{"time":96546,"text":"that are able to hold onto the flower and vibrate it,"},{"time":99669,"text":"and they do this by shaking their flight muscles"},{"time":102261,"text":"at a frequency similar to the musical note C."},{"time":106813,"text":"So they vibrate the flower, they sonicate it,"},{"time":109399,"text":"and that releases the pollen in this efficient swoosh,"},{"time":112446,"text":"and the pollen gathers all over the fuzzy bee's body,"},{"time":115185,"text":"and she takes it home as food."},{"time":117682,"text":"Tomato growers now put bumblebee colonies"},{"time":120523,"text":"inside the greenhouse to pollinate the tomatoes"},{"time":123054,"text":"because they get much more efficient pollination"},{"time":125417,"text":"when it's done naturally"},{"time":126912,"text":"and they get better quality tomatoes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130474,"text":"So there's other, maybe more personal reasons,"},{"time":134061,"text":"to care about bees."},{"time":135484,"text":"There's over 20,000 species of bees in the world,"},{"time":139656,"text":"and they're absolutely gorgeous."},{"time":142662,"text":"These bees spend the majority of their life cycle"},{"time":145281,"text":"hidden in the ground or within a hollow stem"},{"time":148101,"text":"and very few of these beautiful species"},{"time":150801,"text":"have evolved highly social behavior like honeybees."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154234,"text":"Now honeybees tend to be the charismatic representative"},{"time":157854,"text":"for the other 19,900-plus species"},{"time":161023,"text":"because there's something about honeybees"},{"time":163664,"text":"that draws people into their world."},{"time":166513,"text":"Humans have been drawn to honeybees"},{"time":168960,"text":"since early recorded history,"},{"time":170676,"text":"mostly to harvest their honey,"},{"time":172152,"text":"which is an amazing natural sweetener."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175611,"text":"I got drawn into the honeybee world"},{"time":177399,"text":"completely by a fluke."},{"time":179484,"text":"I was 18 years old and bored,"},{"time":181806,"text":"and I picked up a book in the library on bees"},{"time":184668,"text":"and I spent the night reading it."},{"time":186910,"text":"I had never thought about insects"},{"time":188837,"text":"living in complex societies."},{"time":190560,"text":"It was like the best of science fiction come true."},{"time":193962,"text":"And even stranger, there were these people,"},{"time":196856,"text":"these beekeepers, that loved their bees like they were family,"},{"time":200847,"text":"and when I put down the book, I knew I had to see this for myself."},{"time":204150,"text":"So I went to work for a commercial beekeeper,"},{"time":206635,"text":"a family that owned 2,000 hives of bees in New Mexico."},{"time":210832,"text":"And I was permanently hooked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214239,"text":"Honeybees can be considered a super-organism,"},{"time":217553,"text":"where the colony is the organism"},{"time":219709,"text":"and it's comprised of 40,000 to 50,000"},{"time":222441,"text":"individual bee organisms."},{"time":225369,"text":"Now this society has no central authority."},{"time":228701,"text":"Nobody's in charge."},{"time":230297,"text":"So how they come to collective decisions,"},{"time":232642,"text":"and how they allocate their tasks and divide their labor,"},{"time":235622,"text":"how they communicate where the flowers are,"},{"time":238104,"text":"all of their collective social behaviors are mindblowing."},{"time":242268,"text":"My personal favorite, and one that I've studied for many years,"},{"time":246036,"text":"is their system of healthcare."},{"time":247981,"text":"So bees have social healthcare."},{"time":251466,"text":"So in my lab, we study how bees keep themselves healthy."},{"time":255736,"text":"For example, we study hygiene,"},{"time":258075,"text":"where some bees are able to locate and weed out"},{"time":260961,"text":"sick individuals from the nest, from the colony,"},{"time":264128,"text":"and it keeps the colony healthy."},{"time":266592,"text":"And more recently, we've been studying resins"},{"time":270019,"text":"that bees collect from plants."},{"time":272128,"text":"So bees fly to some plants and they scrape"},{"time":275311,"text":"these very, very sticky resins off the leaves,"},{"time":277967,"text":"and they take them back to the nest"},{"time":279545,"text":"where they cement them into the nest architecture"},{"time":282411,"text":"where we call it propolis."},{"time":284936,"text":"We've found that propolis is a natural disinfectant."},{"time":289558,"text":"It's a natural antibiotic."},{"time":291502,"text":"It kills off bacteria and molds and other germs"},{"time":294681,"text":"within the colony,"},{"time":296283,"text":"and so it bolsters the colony health and their social immunity."},{"time":300246,"text":"Humans have known about the power of propolis"},{"time":303537,"text":"since biblical times."},{"time":305184,"text":"We've been harvesting propolis out of bee colonies"},{"time":308534,"text":"for human medicine,"},{"time":310586,"text":"but we didn't know how good it was for the bees."},{"time":314250,"text":"So honeybees have these remarkable natural defenses"},{"time":318303,"text":"that have kept them healthy and thriving"},{"time":320992,"text":"for over 50 million years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325249,"text":"So seven years ago, when honeybee colonies"},{"time":328598,"text":"were reported to be dying en masse,"},{"time":330397,"text":"first in the United States,"},{"time":332369,"text":"it was clear that there was something really, really wrong."},{"time":336182,"text":"In our collective conscience, in a really primal way,"},{"time":339668,"text":"we know we can't afford to lose bees."},{"time":342854,"text":"So what's going on?"},{"time":345969,"text":"Bees are dying from multiple and interacting causes,"},{"time":350058,"text":"and I'll go through each of these."},{"time":352540,"text":"The bottom line is,"},{"time":354393,"text":"bees dying reflects a flowerless landscape"},{"time":358445,"text":"and a dysfunctional food system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361934,"text":"Now we have the best data on honeybees,"},{"time":363926,"text":"so I'll use them as an example."},{"time":365782,"text":"In the United States, bees in fact have been"},{"time":369275,"text":"in decline since World War II."},{"time":372139,"text":"We have half the number of managed hives"},{"time":374413,"text":"in the United States now compared to 1945."},{"time":377427,"text":"We're down to about two million hives of bees, we think."},{"time":381078,"text":"And the reason is, after World War II,"},{"time":383824,"text":"we changed our farming practices."},{"time":387152,"text":"We stopped planting cover crops."},{"time":389991,"text":"We stopped planting clover and alfalfa,"},{"time":392734,"text":"which are natural fertilizers that fix nitrogen in the soil,"},{"time":396580,"text":"and instead we started using synthetic fertilizers."},{"time":400184,"text":"Clover and alfalfa are highly nutritious food plants for bees."},{"time":405728,"text":"And after World War II, we started using herbicides"},{"time":409182,"text":"to kill off the weeds in our farms."},{"time":411679,"text":"Many of these weeds are flowering plants"},{"time":414460,"text":"that bees require for their survival."},{"time":417393,"text":"And we started growing larger and larger crop monocultures."},{"time":422964,"text":"Now we talk about food deserts,"},{"time":425529,"text":"places in our cities, neighborhoods that have no grocery stores."},{"time":429779,"text":"The very farms that used to sustain bees"},{"time":433822,"text":"are now agricultural food deserts,"},{"time":436578,"text":"dominated by one or two plant species"},{"time":439001,"text":"like corn and soybeans."},{"time":441590,"text":"Since World War II, we have been systematically"},{"time":444495,"text":"eliminating many of the flowering plants"},{"time":447394,"text":"that bees need for their survival."},{"time":450946,"text":"And these monocultures extend even to crops"},{"time":453844,"text":"that are good for bees, like almonds."},{"time":456391,"text":"Fifty years ago, beekeepers would take a few colonies,"},{"time":460377,"text":"hives of bees into the almond orchards, for pollination,"},{"time":463388,"text":"and also because the pollen in an almond blossom"},{"time":467320,"text":"is really high in protein. It's really good for bees."},{"time":471500,"text":"Now, the scale of almond monoculture"},{"time":475497,"text":"demands that most of our nation's bees,"},{"time":478049,"text":"over 1.5 million hives of bees,"},{"time":480785,"text":"be transported across the nation"},{"time":483777,"text":"to pollinate this one crop."},{"time":486128,"text":"And they're trucked in in semi-loads,"},{"time":488773,"text":"and they must be trucked out,"},{"time":491103,"text":"because after bloom, the almond orchards"},{"time":493842,"text":"are a vast and flowerless landscape."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499052,"text":"Bees have been dying over the last 50 years,"},{"time":501518,"text":"and we're planting more crops that need them."},{"time":505323,"text":"There has been a 300 percent increase in crop production"},{"time":509507,"text":"that requires bee pollination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513311,"text":"And then there's pesticides."},{"time":516337,"text":"After World War II, we started using pesticides"},{"time":519681,"text":"on a large scale, and this became necessary"},{"time":522245,"text":"because of the monocultures that put out a feast"},{"time":526039,"text":"for crop pests."},{"time":528332,"text":"Recently, researchers from Penn State University"},{"time":531273,"text":"have started looking at the pesticide residue"},{"time":534570,"text":"in the loads of pollen that bees carry home as food,"},{"time":538120,"text":"and they've found that every batch of pollen"},{"time":541711,"text":"that a honeybee collects"},{"time":543718,"text":"has at least six detectable pesticides in it,"},{"time":547505,"text":"and this includes every class of insecticides,"},{"time":551548,"text":"herbicides, fungicides,"},{"time":554391,"text":"and even inert and unlabeled ingredients"},{"time":557971,"text":"that are part of the pesticide formulation"},{"time":560543,"text":"that can be more toxic than the active ingredient."},{"time":564765,"text":"This small bee is holding up a large mirror."},{"time":570407,"text":"How much is it going to take to contaminate humans?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":574855,"text":"One of these class of insecticides,"},{"time":577835,"text":"the neonicontinoids,"},{"time":579210,"text":"is making headlines around the world right now."},{"time":581470,"text":"You've probably heard about it."},{"time":582916,"text":"This is a new class of insecticides."},{"time":584974,"text":"It moves through the plant so that a crop pest,"},{"time":588133,"text":"a leaf-eating insect,"},{"time":589576,"text":"would take a bite of the plant"},{"time":590810,"text":"and get a lethal dose and die."},{"time":594150,"text":"If one of these neonics, we call them,"},{"time":596973,"text":"is applied in a high concentration,"},{"time":599427,"text":"such as in this ground application,"},{"time":601689,"text":"enough of the compound moves through the plant"},{"time":604157,"text":"and gets into the pollen and the nectar,"},{"time":606369,"text":"where a bee can consume, in this case,"},{"time":608473,"text":"a high dose of this neurotoxin"},{"time":611491,"text":"that makes the bee twitch and die."},{"time":615640,"text":"In most agricultural settings, on most of our farms,"},{"time":618813,"text":"it's only the seed that's coated with the insecticide,"},{"time":622756,"text":"and so a smaller concentration moves through the plant"},{"time":625747,"text":"and gets into the pollen and nectar,"},{"time":627715,"text":"and if a bee consumes this lower dose,"},{"time":630258,"text":"either nothing happens"},{"time":631600,"text":"or the bee becomes intoxicated and disoriented"},{"time":635188,"text":"and she may not find her way home."},{"time":638900,"text":"And on top of everything else, bees have"},{"time":641032,"text":"their own set of diseases and parasites."},{"time":643300,"text":"Public enemy number one for bees is this thing."},{"time":646160,"text":"It's called varroa destructor."},{"time":648465,"text":"It's aptly named."},{"time":649569,"text":"It's this big, blood-sucking parasite"},{"time":652181,"text":"that compromises the bee's immune system"},{"time":654555,"text":"and circulates viruses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657326,"text":"Let me put this all together for you."},{"time":660255,"text":"I don't know what it feels like to a bee"},{"time":662922,"text":"to have a big, bloodsucking parasite running around on it,"},{"time":665623,"text":"and I don't know what it feels like to a bee to have a virus,"},{"time":668762,"text":"but I do know what it feels like when I have a virus, the flu,"},{"time":673890,"text":"and I know how difficult it is for me to get"},{"time":677122,"text":"to the grocery store to get good nutrition."},{"time":679911,"text":"But what if I lived in a food desert?"},{"time":682957,"text":"And what if I had to travel a long distance"},{"time":685452,"text":"to get to the grocery store,"},{"time":687325,"text":"and I finally got my weak body out there"},{"time":690199,"text":"and I consumed, in my food,"},{"time":692343,"text":"enough of a pesticide, a neurotoxin,"},{"time":695144,"text":"that I couldn't find my way home?"},{"time":697900,"text":"And this is what we mean by multiple"},{"time":701087,"text":"and interacting causes of death."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704790,"text":"And it's not just our honeybees."},{"time":706979,"text":"All of our beautiful wild species of bees"},{"time":709854,"text":"are at risk, including those tomato-pollinating bumblebees."},{"time":714025,"text":"These bees are providing backup for our honeybees."},{"time":717576,"text":"They're providing the pollination insurance"},{"time":719626,"text":"alongside our honeybees."},{"time":721244,"text":"We need all of our bees."}]},{"cues":[{"time":723667,"text":"So what are we going to do?"},{"time":726208,"text":"What are we going to do about this big bee bummer"},{"time":728622,"text":"that we've created?"},{"time":730885,"text":"It turns out, it's hopeful. It's hopeful."},{"time":734702,"text":"Every one of you out there can help bees"},{"time":738285,"text":"in two very direct and easy ways."},{"time":742750,"text":"Plant bee-friendly flowers,"},{"time":745705,"text":"and don't contaminate these flowers,"},{"time":747838,"text":"this bee food, with pesticides."},{"time":750500,"text":"So go online and search for flowers"},{"time":753834,"text":"that are native to your area and plant them."},{"time":757246,"text":"Plant them in a pot on your doorstep."},{"time":759369,"text":"Plant them in your front yard, in your lawns,"},{"time":761943,"text":"in your boulevards."},{"time":763473,"text":"Campaign to have them planted in public gardens,"},{"time":767086,"text":"community spaces, meadows."},{"time":769667,"text":"Set aside farmland."},{"time":771416,"text":"We need a beautiful diversity of flowers"},{"time":774116,"text":"that blooms over the entire growing season,"},{"time":776287,"text":"from spring to fall."},{"time":778181,"text":"We need roadsides seeded in flowers for our bees,"},{"time":781879,"text":"but also for migrating butterflies and birds"},{"time":785333,"text":"and other wildlife."},{"time":787309,"text":"And we need to think carefully about putting back in"},{"time":790749,"text":"cover crops to nourish our soil"},{"time":793934,"text":"and nourish our bees."},{"time":796955,"text":"And we need to diversify our farms."},{"time":800218,"text":"We need to plant flowering crop borders and hedge rows"},{"time":804000,"text":"to disrupt the agricultural food desert"},{"time":807856,"text":"and begin to correct the dysfunctional food system"},{"time":811146,"text":"that we've created."}]},{"cues":[{"time":813377,"text":"So maybe it seems like a really small countermeasure"},{"time":816761,"text":"to a big, huge problem -- just go plant flowers --"},{"time":819779,"text":"but when bees have access to good nutrition,"},{"time":822807,"text":"we have access to good nutrition"},{"time":824993,"text":"through their pollination services."},{"time":827408,"text":"And when bees have access to good nutrition,"},{"time":829944,"text":"they're better able to engage their own natural defenses,"},{"time":833543,"text":"their healthcare,"},{"time":834961,"text":"that they have relied on for millions of years."},{"time":839059,"text":"So the beauty of helping bees this way, for me,"},{"time":843908,"text":"is that every one of us needs to behave"},{"time":848358,"text":"a little bit more like a bee society, an insect society,"},{"time":853138,"text":"where each of our individual actions"},{"time":856170,"text":"can contribute to a grand solution,"},{"time":859276,"text":"an emergent property,"},{"time":860963,"text":"that's much greater than the mere sum"},{"time":862944,"text":"of our individual actions."},{"time":865689,"text":"So let the small act of planting flowers"},{"time":870839,"text":"and keeping them free of pesticides"},{"time":874166,"text":"be the driver of large-scale change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":878381,"text":"On behalf of the bees, thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881417,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":885540,"text":"Chris Anderson: Thank you. Just a quick question."},{"time":889508,"text":"The latest numbers on the die-off of bees,"},{"time":892664,"text":"is there any sign of things bottoming out?"},{"time":894892,"text":"What's your hope/depression level on this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":897671,"text":"Maria Spivak: Yeah."},{"time":898285,"text":"At least in the United States,"},{"time":900238,"text":"an average of 30 percent of all bee hives"},{"time":902590,"text":"are lost every winter."},{"time":904717,"text":"About 20 years ago,"},{"time":906522,"text":"we were at a 15-percent loss."},{"time":908858,"text":"So it's getting precarious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":910979,"text":"CA: That's not 30 percent a year, that's --\nMS: Yes, thirty percent a year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":913586,"text":"CA: Thirty percent a year.\nMS: But then beekeepers are able to divide their colonies"},{"time":917140,"text":"and so they can maintain the same number,"},{"time":919790,"text":"they can recuperate some of their loss."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922111,"text":"We're kind of at a tipping point."},{"time":923729,"text":"We can't really afford to lose that many more."},{"time":926598,"text":"We need to be really appreciative"},{"time":928418,"text":"of all the beekeepers out there. Plant flowers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":931771,"text":"CA: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":932921,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}